==Trivia==
*Fortunato's name and examine text are references to the {{Wp|Edgar Allan Poe}} story "{{Wp|The Cask of Amontillado}}". The character, Fortunato, was a self-proclaimed wine expert and a member of the masonic lodge. Later, his enemy, Montresor, gets him drunk and seals him into a wall using his skills as a mason.
*''Fortunato'' is Italian for "''the fortunate one''".

